headline: Circle earnings, CPI, comments from Fed's Bostic: What to Watch
summary: Yahoo Finance Markets Reporter Josh Schafer takes a look at the top stories for investors to watch next week, starting Monday, Aug. 11. A fresh slate of earnings will be out, including from Oklo (OKLO) and Plug Power (PLUG) on Monday, Circle (CRCL) and CoreWeave (CRWV) on Tuesday, Brinker (EAT) and Cisco (CSCO) on Wednesday, and Deere & Company (DE) and Birkenstock (BIRK) on Thursday. Plenty of fresh economic data will be released, including the Consumer Price Index (CPI) and NFIB Small Business Optimism Indexon Tuesday, the Producer Price Index (PPI) on Thursday, and retail sales and preliminary consumer sentiment on Friday. Lots of Federal Reserve commentary is coming as well, with Atlanta Fed President Raphael Bostic delivering remarks on Wednesday and Richmond Fed President Tom Barkin speaking on Thursday. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Asking for a Trend.
